# Testing Patterns Overview

## Architecture

Our testing architecture follows a comprehensive approach:

- Unit testing
- Integration testing
- End-to-end testing
- Performance testing
- Accessibility testing

## Core Technologies

- Vitest for unit testing
- React Testing Library
- Playwright for E2E
- MSW for API mocking
- Testing utilities

## Pattern Categories

### 1. Unit Testing

- Component testing
- Hook testing
- Utility testing
- State testing
- Error testing

### 2. Integration Testing

- API integration
- Database testing
- Service integration
- State integration
- Cache testing

### 3. End-to-End Testing

- User flows
- Critical paths
- Cross-browser testing
- Mobile testing
- Visual regression

### 4. Performance Testing

- Load testing
- Stress testing
- Memory leaks
- Bundle size
- Runtime performance

### 5. Test Infrastructure

- Test setup
- Test utilities
- Test data
- Mocking
- CI integration

### 6. Test Monitoring

- Coverage tracking
- Performance metrics
- Test analytics
- Failure analysis
- Quality metrics

## Best Practices

### 1. Test Organization

- Clear structure
- Consistent naming
- Proper isolation
- Shared utilities
- Maintainable setup

### 2. Test Coverage

- Critical paths
- Edge cases
- Error scenarios
- Performance
- Accessibility

### 3. Test Efficiency

- Fast execution
- Parallel running
- Minimal setup
- Proper cleanup
- Resource management

### 4. Test Quality

- Readable tests
- Reliable tests
- Maintainable tests
- Useful failures
- Clear documentation

